cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.DS, cs.RO, cs.SY

This paper is about deep reinforcement learning, specifically the use of target networks in Q-learning algorithms. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), which includes topics such as deep learning and reinforcement learning. The paper also discusses theoretical analysis of the algorithm, which could fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the use of Q-values and Markov decision processes suggests that cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) could be a relevant category. The application of the algorithm to robotics (as mentioned in the abstract) could also place it in cs.RO (Robotics). Finally, the use of reinforcement learning in control systems could make cs.SY (Systems and Control) a possible category as well.
